org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser

Class FormulaParserLL3

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.FormulaParserLL3
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FormulaParserLL3Constants, IFormulaParser

    public class FormulaParserLL3
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFormulaParser, FormulaParserLL3Constants
    Class used to parse infix mathematical formula and returns a representation of it as an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)..

    Support almost the same syntax as defined in the LibSBML L3 parser. The things not supported for now are the units associated with numbers.

    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    $Rev: 1639 $
    Author:
    Alexander Dörr, Nicolas Rodriguez

      • createModulo

        private ASTNode createModulo(ASTNode leftChild,
                   ASTNode rightChild)
        Returns a piecewise ASTNode representing the modulo operation between the left and right child given.

        The fomula produced for 'a % b' or modulo(a, b) is 'piecewise(floor(a/b), gt(a/b, 0), ceil(a/b))'

        Parameters:
        leftChild -
        rightChild -
        Returns:
        a piecewise ASTNode representing the modulo operation between the left and right child given.
        See Also:
        http://sbml.org/Documents/FAQ#Why_can.27t_I_use_the_.3Crem.3E_operator_in_SBML_MathML.3F
